summary: An ordinance repealing Ordinance No. 18689 entitled: "An ordinance relating to and providing for the improvement of West Hinds Street, in the City of Seattle, from California Avenue to 51st Avenue Southwest, by grading and curbing the same, and by constructing the necessary drainage, all in accordance with Resolution No. 1371 of the city council of the City of Seattle; and providing payment therefor by the mode of "Payment in Bonds", as provided by the laws of the State of Washington and the Charter and Ordinances of the City of Seattle" approved June 15, 1908.
